          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC",
                  "THCOL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Thermal neutrons from the thermal column",
                "of heavy-water reactor. Neutron beam filtered through",
                "monocrystalline silicon, the cross-section with 8 cm",
                "in diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.902
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Isotopic composition of the",
                "sample are 234U (1.1%), 235U (90.2%), 236U (0.3%) and",
                "238U (8.4%). The thick uranium with 16 mm in",
                "diameter and 0.4-0.8 g/cm2 thick was wrapped by pure",
                "aluminium foil with 5 mg/cm2 thick. The thin standard",
                "uranium with 16 mm in diameter and 0.3-0.4 mg/cm2",
                "thick was electrodeposited on the platinum foil with",
                "0.10-0.15 mm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The volume of P-type coaxial HPGe detector is",
                "110 cm3. For gamma energy 1332.5 keV the gamma-energy",
                "resolution FWHM is 1.8 keV. The distance between",
                "detector and sample can be adjusted. At a distance of",
                "31.6 cm, the detection efficiency was calibrated",
                "relatively using Eu-152, and was calibrated",
                "absolutely using various standard gamma sources,",
                "which were Mn-54, Co-57, Zn-65, Cd-109 and Cs-137.",
                "The ratio of detection efficiency between distance of",
                "1.3 cm and 31.6 cm, was determined using Cr-51, Mn-54,",
                "Zn-65, Zr-95, Ru-103, Cs-137, Ba-140, Ce-141 and",
                "Ce-144. The uncertainty of efficiency is less than 2%",
                "at 1.3 cm distance."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Double-fission chamber were used to measure",
                "the absolute fission rate."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ABSFY",
                "FPGAM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Decay gamma spectrum area were determined with SPAN",
